{
  "texts": [
    "In other words, where such detectors are successful, they will sometimes render judgments that are in tension with the perceptions of human observers.",
    "An ADD might declare a video that appears real to human observers to be inauthentic, and vice-versa.",
    "Thus, on the face of things, these technologies will only help humans to better distinguish between deepfakes and non-deepfakes, where humans trust foot_1 these technologies more than their own senses.",
    "This initial gloss is too quick.",
    "One might put greater trust in one's own faculties than the abilities of an automated system, but nonetheless treat unexpected outputs of that system as grounds for examining a given video more closely."
  ]
}